1 English Approval of the Minutes of the previous sitting 
2 English The Minutes of yesterday 's sitting have been distributed . 
3 English Are there any comments ? 
4 English Mr President , on Monday I made a point of order about President Nicole Fontaine 's reported comments in the British press regarding her recent visit with Her Majesty Queen Elizabeth II . 
5 English A British Labour Member of this House , Mr Miller , repeated what were purported to be the Queen 's remarks , not once but three times , on Monday , on Tuesday and on Wednesday . 
6 English He sought to drag the Queen into a political controversy and to use her name to score cheap political points . 
7 English Mr President , it may be that President Fontaine was unfamiliar with the British rules of protocol which obtain in such matters , but Mr Miller has no such excuse . 
8 English He knows perfectly well that ours is a non - political Head of State . 
9 English He knows perfectly well that for nearly fifty years she has scrupulously avoided engaging in controversial political issues . 
10 English He knows perfectly well that she cannot come to this House to set the record straight . 
11 English His behaviour is a disgrace and a scandal . 
12 English Mr President , I am proud to be British but today I am ashamed to share my nationality with that man . 
13 English Has he no shame ? 
14 English Has he no respect ? 
15 English Has he no decency or honour at all ? 
16 English Mr President , I wish to use this point of order to speak in my capacity as chairman of the delegation for relations with the countries of Central America and Mexico . 
17 English As you will be aware , elections were held in Mexico last Sunday . 
18 English Yesterday the delegation which I chair met and discussed a report drawn up by our fellow Members who had been to Mexico to act as observers at these elections on behalf of this Parliament . 
19 English Mr President , I would ask you to see if the President of this Parliament could forward our resolution , the complete text of which you will receive today , to the Mexican authorities . 
20 English Mr President , ladies and gentlemen , I want to draw your attention to something really annoying in connection with the Minutes . 
21 English The - & # x2018 ; Texts Adopted & # x2019 ; - also form part of the Minutes . 
22 English I pointed out yesterday during the vote on the directive to combat money laundering the English translation of Article 6 ( 3 ) needs to be corrected to bring it in line with Amendment No 26, because the English translation is wrong . 
23 English In the middle of the second paragraph of the English version there is only a reference to representation in legal proceedings , but no reference to legal consultants , as there is in the German text . 
24 English That is a key point in this directive and since the Council working group is working on the basis of the English text it is quite crucial to correct this text . 
25 English I had already complained about this in committee vis à vis the language services . 
26 English At the time the committee decided not to table an amendment because the German text is the original version , as drafted by the rapporteur . 
27 English I complained about this yesterday -- the situation was not remedied -- and today is the third time I am complaining about it ! 
28 English I do think the services of this House should work more carefully on such key questions and it really is intolerable that despite my criticism yesterday the Minutes have got the text wrong again ! 
29 English I would ask you get to the bottom of this matter , to sort out this most important aspect of the directive and to please correct this in the English translation ! 
30 English Mr President , yesterday we received a communication on yellow paper from the vice - president , with some nuts attached to it . 
31 English This note was about supporting the export of products from Vanuatu , a developing country in the Pacific . 
32 English I think that is a very good idea and quite right . 
33 English And I am quite happy to support it . 
34 English But what rather puzzles me is that in it the vice - president quite explicitly stated that it is illegal to import these nuts into the European Union . 
35 English So I must ask this vice - president to explain how these nuts came to be illegally imported , since it was he who delivered them to us ! 
