1592 English Child soldiers in Uganda 
1593 English Madam President , Commissioner , one could say a lot about this issue . 
1594 English Firstly , I hope , in particular , that the Council and the Commission will be active when it comes to also taking up this issue in the Security Council when the action plan concerning children in armed conflicts will be debated at the end of this month . 
1595 English Secondly , we have today noted with satisfaction that attempts are being made to reach a common solution to at least one other conflict regarding child soldiers . 
1596 English This solution is the so - called diamond resolution in the Security Council . 
1597 English Thirdly , we can confirm that we have made a certain amount of general progress with regard to child soldiers . 
1598 English We have the voluntary Supplementary Protocol against Child Soldiers and the Activities in Africa . 
1599 English I would ask the House to support this resolution . 
1600 English I would also like the EU jointly to take up the issue in the Security Council at the end of this month during the follow - up to the general debate on children in armed conflicts . 
1601 English Madam President , the situation in Northern Uganda and Southern Sudan is the setting for the drama of the child - soldiers . 
1602 English The aim of my speech and of the resolution which has just been tabled is to prompt Parliament and the institutions to adopt ongoing initiatives which do more than just respond to moments of crisis . 
1603 English There has been continuous armed conflict in this region for the last 30 years ; civil society has been completely destroyed and different groups of rebels have been massacring the peoples of Northern Uganda for over 12 years . 
1604 English Their favourite victims are children and adolescents because they are vulnerable and easily influenced . 
1605 English To date , approximately 60 % of the soldiers in the Lord 's Resistance Army are children under the age of 16 . 
1606 English The strategy is precisely to manipulate the children and subject them to brutal force so that they will in turn be able to kill and torture others . 
1607 English Adolescent girls are given to the rebels as wives , but the most noticeable thing is that not even the Nairobi Agreements between Uganda and the Sudan last December have caused the LRA to change its attitude . 
1608 English During the last few days , I have had the opportunity to talk to one of the girls who has escaped from the fields of Southern Sudan , who confirmed that the LRA has no intention of changing its position . 
1609 English Further evidence of this is the funeral of John Baptista Ochaia , the representative of the Chairman of Kitgum district council , who died the day before yesterday from wounds received during an LRA ambush , which took place today in Uganda . 
1610 English It is therefore unacceptable that the European authorities and many commercial entities should maintain an attitude almost of tacit approval of this situation , without making any attempt to break the circle which is robbing a generation of its future . 
1611 English Madam President , ladies and gentlemen , war is always cruel , and civil war even more so . 
1612 English However , we have reached another level of barbarism and abjectness when children are used to fight and kill or be killed . 
1613 English In this way , the LRA , the armed resistance , does not hesitate to kidnap seven - year - old boys and subject them to extreme brutality to train them to fight and terrorise villagers . 
1614 English Nor does it hesitate to sexually exploit women and girls . 
1615 English When these children survive , it must be said , they are in any case scarred for life . 
1616 English It takes time , patience and love to restore their hope . 
1617 English This is why we must increase aid and support for UNICEF , which has set up an action programme enabling children to return to a normal life . 
1618 English Madam President , we must also stop pussyfooting around . 
1619 English Sudan must stop supporting the LRA . 
1620 English In my opinion , this amounts to collusion , which makes Sudan just as guilty . 
1621 English And Parliament must intervene to urge the Ugandan Government to find a peaceful solution to this conflict in the north of Uganda , which , let me remind you , has been the cause of 100 000 deaths in 15 years . 
1622 English The whole population is waiting for this solution and all the children are hoping for it . 
1623 English The Security Council must hear this plea . 
1624 English Madam President , I am really pleased that this resolution has come about . 
1625 English I hope that this will encourage the Commission and the Member States to act on this issue . 
1626 English Some weeks ago , a documentary from Southern Sudan was shown on Swedish television . 
